&lt;p&gt;The Director of Product Engineering is responsible for leading the design, development, and delivery of Scion’s internal and resident-facing software tools. This role sits at the intersection of product management, engineering execution, and business strategy—ensuring Scion’s technology platforms drive operational efficiency, enhance resident experience, and scale with portfolio growth.&lt;br&gt;This leader will build and manage high-performing engineering teams, partner closely with product and operations stakeholders, and establish a modern, scalable technology ecosystem aligned with Scion’s long-term digital strategy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Responsibilities &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Engineering Leadership &amp;amp; Strategy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and execute the engineering vision for Scion’s software platforms, aligned with business objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead, mentor, and grow a team of software engineers, QA, and technical leads.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish best practices for architecture, coding standards, testing, and deployment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive adoption of modern development frameworks, cloud infrastructure, and scalable systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Product &amp;amp; Cross-Functional Partnership&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Product, Analytics, Revenue Management, and Operations teams to translate business needs into technical solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate on product roadmaps, ensuring engineering feasibility, scalability, and performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a key stakeholder in prioritization, balancing speed, quality, and business impact.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Platform Development &amp;amp; Ownership&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee development of internal tools (leasing, operations, reporting, integrations) and resident-facing applications.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure systems integrate seamlessly with third-party platforms (e.g., property management systems, CRMs, payment systems).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive data platform improvements to support analytics, reporting, and decision-making.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Delivery &amp;amp; Execution&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement agile development processes to improve speed, predictability, and transparency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own delivery timelines, resource planning, and execution quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor KPIs such as system performance, uptime, deployment frequency, and defect rates.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Technology &amp;amp; Architecture&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
